Been waiting 15 years for promotion.
I know some have enjoyed it here (obviously there’ve been great moments), but I personally won’t miss the championship. It’s all felt like a bad dream to me.

snippet.textDisplay:
I've followed Leeds for fifty years. Long time since I felt such a buzz; it's the way the entire team seems to be able to circulate and exchange forward/back R/L positions. Makes them very fluid yet very unpredictable. Not exactly the finished product yet but it's suddenly becoming clearer what MB is trying to achieve. We'll be having Bamford doing spells in goal and Meslier up front next.
That Ayling though... my word, I haven't seen a volley like that since Lorimer's days.
